Citation.sAbstract: Density, (q), and speed of sound, (u), from T = 288.15 to T = 308.15 K, and excess molar enthalpies, (hE) at T = 298.15 K, have been  measured over the entire composition range for (methyl tert-butyl ether + 1-butanol + n-hexane). In addition, excess molar volumes, VE,  and excess isentropic compressibility, jEs  , were calculated from experimental data. Finally, experimental excess enthalpies results are  compared with the estimations obtained by applying the group-contribution models of UNIFAC (in the versions of Dang and Tassios,  Larsen et al., Gmehling et al.), and DISQUAC.
Citation.sTitle: Excess enthalpy, density, and speed of sound determination for the ternary mixture (methyl tert-butyl ether + 1-butanol + n-hexane)
